      • getExpectedPreviousToken

        public String getExpectedPreviousToken()
        Returns the expected previous token, or null if not present. If present, the Play directive will only execute if it matches the token of the active stream on the device.
        Returns:
        the expected previous token

      • setExpectedPreviousToken

        public void setExpectedPreviousToken(String expectedPreviousToken)
        This property is required to be set and allowed only when the playBehavior is ENQUEUE. Setting this property when playBehavior is any other value ( REPLACE_ALL or REPLACE_ENQUEUED) causes an error.
        Parameters:
        expectedPreviousToken - an opaque token that represents the expected previous stream.
        See Also:
        getExpectedPreviousToken()

      • getToken
